The problem requires finding the maximum number that satisfies the given constraints and is less than or equal to k. We can solve this problem by iterating from 0 to log2(power) (logarithm base 2 of power), where power is the result of Math.pow(2, x). For each iteration, we multiply the result by (1L << i), where i is the current iteration index. Finally, divide the result by (1L << (power - k)).

This solution has a time complexity of O(log(power)) because we only iterate log2(power) times. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a single variable for the result. The energy implications are low because the algorithm is efficient and requires minimal resources.

